question.title: Java applet deadlock on Chrome on Win 7 64 with either JRE 1.6.0.29 or 1.7.0.1

node.contents: We've seen similar behaviour in Safari on OS X, very intermittently.

astNode.text: We've seen similar behaviour in Safari on OS X, very intermittently.

node.contents: I'm writing an an applet and it sometimes hangs before it even enters init() when running under Chrome (14.0.835.202 m) on Windows 7 64.

astNode.text: I'm writing an an applet and it sometimes hangs before it even enters init() when running under Chrome (14.0.835.202 m) on Windows 7 64.

node.contents: I'm using the following bit of code to create the applet (created within the <body> element), and under FF (and even Chrome when running on XP 32-bit) it runs fine:
